---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BrandMark from '../components/BrandMark.astro';
import { loadStats } from '../lib/stats';
import { formatBytes, formatNumber } from '../lib/ssr';

const stats = loadStats();
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — Essenfont"
  description="Essenfont is a universal Unicode 17 font — one redistributable OpenType file covering every assigned codepoint, assembled from OFL-licensed donor fonts."
  canonical="/about"
>
  <article class="about container">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>One font, every codepoint</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Essenfont</strong> is a real font — not a library or a service. A single
        redistributable OpenType Collection (OTC) that covers every assigned Unicode 17
        codepoint ({formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)} characters across
        {stats.unicode.blockCount} blocks), built from {stats.donorCount} canonical
        OFL-licensed donor fonts.
      </p>
      <p>
        There is no UFO source, no hand-designed glyphs. Every glyph is vector-extracted
        from canonical donor fonts — Noto, Full-Sung, UniHieroglyphica, and more. The
        build is purely an assembly pipeline: read donors → partition by plane → stitch
        into subfonts → pack into a collection.
      </p>

      <h2>The name</h2>
      <p>
        <em>Essen</em> — German for "to eat" — because a universal font is meant to be
        consumed everywhere. The "font" is the object. Together: a font that eats every
        script.
      </p>

      <h2 id="logo">The mark</h2>
    </section>

    <!-- ─── Logo philosophy ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="logo-philosophy">
      <div class="logo-gallery">
        <figure class="logo-figure logo-figure--hero">
          <BrandMark size="xl" animated={false} interactive={true} alt="Essenfont logo, blue variant" />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="mono">Default · Blue</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="logo-figure">
          <img src="/img/logo/essenfont-dark-blue-256.png" alt="Dark mode, blue" width="128" height="128" />
          <figcaption><span class="mono">Dark · Blue</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="logo-figure">
          <img src="/img/logo/essenfont-dark-red-256.png" alt="Dark mode, red" width="128" height="128" />
          <figcaption><span class="mono">Dark · Red</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="logo-figure">
          <img src="/img/logo/essenfont-light-blue-256.png" alt="Light mode, blue" width="128" height="128" />
          <figcaption><span class="mono">Light · Blue</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="logo-figure">
          <img src="/img/logo/essenfont-light-red-256.png" alt="Light mode, red" width="128" height="128" />
          <figcaption><span class="mono">Light · Red</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="prose logo-prose">
        <p>
          The Essenfont mark is shaped as the hexagram <strong>Gen</strong>
          (<span class="glyph-big">☶</span>), the fifty-second hexagram of the
          I&nbsp;Ching. <em>Gen</em> means <em>mountain</em> — stillness, the root from
          which all creation grows. The mountain does not move; everything else moves
          around it. So too does a universal typeface anchor every script in Unicode
          while remaining itself unchanged.
        </p>

        <h3>The empty that provides utility</h3>
        <p>
          Look at the negative space inside the hexagram's lines: it forms the letter
          <strong>E</strong>. This is no accident. Laozi wrote in the <em>Dao De
          Jing</em>:
        </p>
        <blockquote class="dao-quote">
          <p>
            Thirty spokes share one hub —<br/>
            it is the emptiness at the center that makes the wheel useful.<br/>
            Shape clay into a vessel —<br/>
            it is the void inside that holds what you pour.<br/>
            Cut doors and windows for a room —<br/>
            it is the gap that lets the light in.
          </p>
          <cite>— Dao De Jing, ch. 11</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          The logo's translucent, glass-like quality embodies this principle.
          Essenfont is transparent: it claims no authorship of its glyphs, takes no
          credit for its donor outlines, and hides nothing about its build pipeline.
          Its usefulness comes from what it <em>contains</em>, not from what it
          <em>is</em> — the empty vessel that holds every script.
        </p>

        <h3>Two colors, one motion</h3>
        <p>
          The logo exists in two color variants — <span class="color-chip color-chip--blue"></span>
          blue (illumination, the calm authority of a clear sky) and
          <span class="color-chip color-chip--red"></span> red (rubrication, the medieval
          practice of marking important initials in vermilion). Together they represent
          motion: the mark shifts from blue to red when you interact with it, just as a
          universal font shifts between scripts without losing its identity. The duality
          echoes the <em>yin</em> and <em>yang</em> — two forces, one mark.
        </p>

        <h3>In darkness, clarity</h3>
        <p>
          In dark mode, the mark sheds its background entirely. The mountain stands alone,
          struck by no surrounding frame. As the Heart Sutra teaches:
        </p>
        <blockquote class="dao-quote">
          <p>
            Form is emptiness, emptiness is form.<br/>
            In darkness, you distinguish both dark and bright more clearly.
          </p>
          <cite>— Prajñāpāramitā Hṛdaya Sūtra</cite>
        </blockquote>
        <p>
          The dark variant is the more striking of the two — not because it adds, but
          because it subtracts. The background falls away, and the mark's essential
          geometry — the mountain, the E, the emptiness at the center — becomes
          unmistakable. What remains when everything unnecessary is removed is what
          was always there.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose">
      <h2>The technical achievement</h2>
      <p>
        The canonical output is <code>Essenfont-Regular.otc</code> ({formatBytes(stats.fontBinaries.otcSizeBytes)}),
        a 10-face OpenType Collection with CFF2 outlines and CBDT color emoji bitmaps.
        The website serves {stats.websiteSubsets.woff2Count} per-block WOFF2 subsets ({formatBytes(stats.websiteSubsets.woff2TotalBytes)} total)
        so visitors don't download the full {formatNumber(stats.unicode.assignedCodepointCount)}-codepoint font just to
        browse one script.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every WOFF2 subset loads in Chrome's OpenType Sanitizer — a goal that required
        13 named fixes across three repos. See the <a href="/engineering">engineering story</a>
        for the full account.
      </p>

      <h2>License</h2>
      <p>
        Essenfont is distributed under the <strong>Open Font License (OFL) 1.1</strong>.
        Each donor's license terms are preserved in the font's <code>name</code> table and
        in the auto-generated <code>LICENSE-SOURCES.md</code>. See the
        <a href="/license">license page</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>Get it</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/download">Download from GitHub Releases</a> or install via Fontist:
      </p>
      <pre><code>fontist install "Essenfont"</code></pre>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem; }
  .page-head { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ef-rose, #0d7377); margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-display, Spectral, serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .prose h2, .logo-prose h3 {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-display, Spectral, serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .logo-prose h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ef-rose, #0d7377);
  }
  .prose p { font-size: 1.0625rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .prose code {
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono, monospace);
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .prose pre {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  .prose pre code { background: none; padding: 0; }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--ef-rose, #0d7377);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  /* ─── Logo philosophy section ──────────────────────────── */
  .logo-philosophy {
    margin: 3rem 0;
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ef-rule, rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.08));
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ef-rule, rgba(26, 24, 21, 0.08));
  }
  .logo-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    align-items: end;
  }
  .logo-figure {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.625rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .logo-figure--hero {
    grid-column: span 1;
  }
  .logo-figure--hero :global(.brand-mark) {
    width: 128px;
    height: 128px;
  }
  .logo-figure img {
    width: 96px;
    height: 96px;
    object-fit: contain;
  }
  .logo-figure figcaption {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ef-text-3, #8a8478);
  }
  .logo-prose {
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .glyph-big {
    font-size: 1.75em;
    line-height: 0;
    vertical-align: -0.1em;
    color: var(--ef-rose, #0d7377);
  }
  .dao-quote {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.75rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--ef-rose, #0d7377);
    background: var(--ef-surface, #f2efe9);
    font-family: var(--spec-font-display, Spectral, serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .dao-quote p { margin: 0; }
  .dao-quote cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: var(--spec-font-mono, monospace);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ef-text-3, #8a8478);
  }
  .color-chip {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 0.75em;
    height: 0.75em;
    border-radius: 50%;
    vertical-align: -0.05em;
    margin-right: 0.15em;
  }
  .color-chip--blue { background: #1a3a8a; }
  .color-chip--red  { background: #9b2d2d; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .logo-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
    .logo-figure img { width: 72px; height: 72px; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .logo-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
</style>
